Vendored from audit-harness@v1.1.4 (tag commit on main post PR #40 merge).

PR #40 closes 4 deferred upstream beads bundled into one focused cleanup
release:

  - iah-gherkin-prev-blank-noise (o9q1): removed bare `prev_blank = 1`
    at top of 3rd awk block in gherkin-lint.sh. Was an always-true awk
    pattern triggering default `{ print }` action, flooding stdout with
    every feature-file line. Variable had zero call sites.

  - iah-gherkin-single-awk-opt (vawm): collapsed process_awk_output()
    from 2 awk subprocesses per call to 1 single-pass via
    `read -r w e < <(awk ...)`. Halves the awk fork count.

  - iah-crap-score-exclusion-dedup (niv8): extracted module-level
    EXCLUDED_DIRS constant (union of prior `ignore` + `prune` sets) in
    crap-score.py. Prior asymmetry: `ignore` had `reports` but lacked
    .next/.nuxt/.cache; `prune` had the opposite. Real latent bug for
    repos with either kind of dir; now consistent.

  - iah-shellcheck-version-pin (v1ds): CI shellcheck pinned to v0.10.0
    via koalaman/shellcheck releases download (parity with ruff pin
    in v1.1.3). SHELLCHECK_VERSION env var is single source of truth.

Plus comment hygiene per PR #40 Gemini review: removed version-history
references from source-code comments (CHANGELOG + git history are the
right places).

